My top priority is creating jobs & investing in the foundation of long-term economic growth in the Pacific Northwest. I look forward to working with my colleagues to advance the #INVESTAct & help the nation’s economy move forward in the wake of the #COVID19 pandemic.

👷🏻‍♀️👷🏾‍♂️The #INVESTAct improves workforce development programs & job training to better prep the next gen of U.S transportation workers. It also includes a bipartisan provision I introduced to promote career opportunities & improve diversity in the transportation workforce.

⛴ Ferries account for 73% of WA’s annual carbon emissions. I teamed up w/@RepDonaldPayne to intro an amendment to establish a 0️⃣- or reduced-emission grant program to help ferries reduce emissions & build supportive infrastructure. @wsferries

One of my provisions in the #INVESTAct designates the Bicycle & Pedestrian Coordinator at state Departments of Transportation as a full-time position to elevate states’ active transportation priorities increase safety & encourage more people to bike and walk outdoors.

2/4 ➡️ Economic Impact Payments (EIP) are not subject to Federal income tax.  ➡️ Receiving the EIP does not take away from your typical refund next year (2020 tax return filed in 2021).
